metadata.name: AEOLUS - Keeper of the Winds
metadata.description: Aeolus is the name of a few different characters in GREEK MYTHOLOGY [Aeolus, the son of Hippotes or Aeolus, the half-human son of Poseidon] but the one most commonly associated with the name is the god of winds. He plays a key role in Homer’s Odyssey, in which he’s also known as the keeper of the winds.
